  <p><em>(A Guide for Curious Kids and Their Tall Friends)</em></p>

  <h2>Welcome, Forest Explorer!</h2>
  <p>Today you're going on a forest walk, which is not the same as a hike.</p>
  <p>A forest walk is slower, quieter, and has more looking up.</p>
  <p>Somewhere above the streams, hidden among branches, lives a very shy fish called the Rocky Mountain Tree Trout. You might not see one - but that's okay! Tree trout are experts at not being seen.</p>

  <h2>Step 1: Find the Right Place</h2>
  <p>Look for:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Tall pine or fir trees</li>
    <li>A cold, clear stream nearby</li>
    <li>Mossy rocks and squishy ground</li>
  </ul>
  <p>If the forest feels calm and a little mysterious, you're in the right spot.</p>

  <h2>Step 2: Use Your Forest Senses</h2>
